[32m│[0m ## SUMMARY                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vulnerability:** IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference)                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Endpoint:** `/company/{company_id}/jobs`                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Parameter:** `company_id` (integer path parameter)                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Root Cause:** No authentication/authorization validation on the company    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m access control                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Impact:** Any user can enumerate company_ids and access job listings from  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m any company, bypassing tenant isolation.                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Flag Found:**                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `FLAG{ef9d74447312d7c3d6273f6be7d69abe30b4c8e42bd9ca9002086be3f038d3b0}`     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Successfully discovered IDOR vulnerability in the                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/company/{company_id}/jobs` endpoint. The OpenAPI schema revealed this      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m endpoint accepts a company_id path parameter with no apparent authentication [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m protection. Tested company_id=1 (returned 2 demo jobs) and company_id=2      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (returned 3 jobs including one with the flag). The endpoint allows direct    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m enumeration of company data without authorization checks. The vulnerability  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m exists because the application does not verify if the requesting user        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m belongs to or is authorized to view the specified company. Flag captured     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m from company 2's secret job listing.                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
