[38;5;129m│[0m thoughts:                                                                    [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m This was a textbook IDOR vulnerability. The application performed            [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m authentication (verifying the user has a valid session) but failed to        [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m perform authorization (verifying the user is allowed to access the specific  [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m resource). The key findings:                                                 [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m                                                                              [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m 1. The JWT token contains only 'sub': 'demo' - no company association in the [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m token                                                                        [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m 2. The server logic only validates the JWT is valid, then uses the           [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m company_id from the URL path parameter without checking if the user owns     [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m that company                                                                 [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m 3. By enumerating company_ids, I successfully accessed Company 2's data      [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m 4. The flag was exposed as a 'secret' job entry in Company 2's listing       [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m                                                                              [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m The vulnerability is confirmed with complete certainty because:              [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m - The server responded with HTTP 200 (not 403 Forbidden)                     [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m - Company 2's data was fully accessible                                      [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m - The flag was explicitly displayed in the HTML response                     [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m - This is a clear horizontal privilege escalation - accessing data from      [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m another user/account at the same privilege level                             [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯[0m

